    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6b2b01b8_641e3bab",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/proto/common.proto",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 26,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-29T02:37:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Exactly, \"The user is expected to keep all other arguments to the RPC the same; if any arguments are different, the API should send an INVALID_ARGUMENT error.\"\n\nThat said, I\u0027m not sure yet how we\u0027ll be able to do this comparison on actual e.g. ListTestResults calls, i.e. how ResultDB will know whether the cursor was a continuation or a new cursor, unless we annotate the requests themselves with some ID to identify them as part of the same sequence and store that information somewhere.\n\n(Also I can make this a string if you prefer.)",
      "parentUuid": "01a88c21_8f4dc00a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 23,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 26,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "0a2b2651901999733141811eafb01f1bde201e0b",
